RACE.RACE_TEXT: HAWTHORNE RACE 1 1M 70Y Dirt CR: 56. Maiden Claiming Purse 15500. FOR MAIDENS, FILLIES AND MARES THREE YEARS OLD AND UPWARD. Three Year Olds, 119 lbs.; Older, 124 lbs. Claiming Price $15,000.
RACE.FOOTNOTES: IZZY'S MONSTER was unhurried early while never far off the pace, raced outside, rallied into the turn to challenge, dueled briefly and drew off under steady urging. HOLY STAR was sent to the front, led around the first turn, pressed inside when headed, bid on the turn to duel briefly, fell back and was no match for the winner. LIL CARRIE D moved up to assume command along the backstretch, bore out badly on the turn, dropped back, went evenly late and held safely for show. BUNNY SHINE settled off the pace while racing inside, lacked a stretch response and did not threaten. PRETTY IN PRADO held a good position to the second turn, tired and gave way. SHE APPEALS HOLY hit the gate and was steadied at the start to be off slowly, fell far back, trailed the field and failed to contend.

RACE.FOOTNOTES: SIERRA HOTEL stalked the pace along the inside, awaited room on the turn, shifted out, bid willingly to duel and drew clear late. LAND MARK DEAL was checked hard entering the first turn, stayed close to the pace, got through along the rail on the second turn, closed willingly, altered course late and was gaining for second. STAR OF KODIAK broke slowly, was crowded and steadied at the start, was allowed to settle and saved ground while racing in the back, advanced on the turn and offered a mild bid only. KENNESAW stalked the pace, was carried out leaving the turn, fell back and gave way. PAYSTER veered out at the start, vied to the second turn, swung wide and gave way. WEST COAST CHROME raced outside while never far off the pace, showed speed to the second turn, tired and stopped. The rider of LAND MARK DEAL claimed foul against the rider of LAVENDER EARLY for alleged interference into the first turn. No change was made.
